# intuition
after looking at this question i realized i can solve the question using sliding window pattern ,then i realized the window size in this question is fixed , so my strategy was to calculate the sum of first subarray and then slide the window and calculate slide window of next subbaray and compare the max sum among the 2 subbarays and repeat this till whole array is traversed 

# approach
assign 2 pointers 
low = 0
high = k - 1
window_sum = 0

calculate sum of first window 

result = 0

loop condition for traversal till end of array (high < len(arr)
       compare result with window total return max of them
            move the pointers high and low 

               check if high is inside the loop:
                   calculate new window total
  return result

#time compexity 
O(n)

#space complexity 
O(1)

#code

class Solution:
    def maxSubarraySum(self, arr, k):
        # code here 
        low = 0
        high = k - 1
        window_sum = 0
        
        for i in range(low, high + 1 , 1):
            window_sum = window_sum + arr[i]
        
        result = window_sum    
        while high < len(arr):
            result = max(window_sum , result)
            low += 1
            high += 1
            
            if high == len(arr):
                break
            else:
                window_sum = window_sum - arr[low-1] + arr[high]
        return result    
        
